
[1]hypocist

   HYP'OCIST, n. [Gr. sub cisto, under the distus.] An inspissated juice
   obtained from the sessile asarum [Cytinus hypocistis,] resembling the
   true Egyptian acacia. The juice is expressed from the unripe fruit and
   evaporated to the consistence of an extract, formed into cakes and
   dried in the sun. It is an astringent, useful in diarrheas and
   hemorrhages.
